Quackwatch Fraud
Featured


Posted on May 30, 2016  by  drowland 



For nearly a century, organized medicine tried to discredit and destroy chiropractic.  On 24 August 1987, a U.S. court ruled that the American Medical Association and its officials were guilty of participating in an illegal conspiracy to destroy the chiropractic profession.
Today, this suppression is being carried on by Quackwatch (www.quackwatch.org) – not only against chiropractic but also every established profession that competes with orthodox medicine – including acupuncture, homeopathy, naturopathy, herbal medicine, orthomolecular medicine, and nutrition.  Quackwatch has gone so far as to discredit the Nobel Prize winning scientists, Dr. Linus Pauling and Dr. Otto Warburg.
Quackwatch is headed by Stephen Barrett, a delicensed medical doctor who proudly admits his intention is to damage practitioners and businesses that dare to make alternative therapies and products available.  Barrett often resorts to libel and character assassination in his false propaganda campaigns.
To be targeted by Quackwatch is really a badge of honor.  If the medical profession considers you that much of a threat, you must be helping many people in ways that they cannot.






